These are Puzzles for 2x6 Level 9

.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-9-1::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: taxi, trike, skateboard, tram, boat, subway
The people have 6 different jobs:  doctor, engineer, freelancer, lawyer, photographer, police-officer
 1. the engineer is not to the right of the person driving the tram##8
 2. the police-officer is not to the left of the doctor##8
 3. the person driving the subway is the police-officer##1
 4. the lawyer is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
 5. the freelancer and the person driving the taxi have different parity positions##9
 6. the person driving the skateboard is on the right of the police-officer##1
 7. the person driving the subway is on the left of the lawyer##1
 8. the engineer is on the left of the person driving the boat##1
 9. the police-officer is not the person driving the boat##6
10. the person driving the boat is somewhere to the left of the person driving the tram##5
11. the person driving the taxi is on the right of the freelancer##1
12. the person driving the trike is not to the right of the engineer##8
13. the person driving the tram is somewhere to the left of the person driving the taxi##5

.:: Answer ::.
|        |      1      |   2    |       3        |   4    |     5      |      6       |
| Food   | trike | boat | subway     | skateboard | tram    | taxi        |
| Job    | engineer    | doctor | police-officer | lawyer | freelancer | photographer |

